Summary and Uses:
Total Hcy is a thiol-containing amino acid, produced by the intracellular demethylation of methionine to
cysteine.
Elevated levels of t Hcy may be used to exclude or confirm deficiencies of vitamin B12 or folate.
It is recommended to test in patients using medications that interfere with folate status (methotrexate,
antiepileptics), vegetarians without  B12 supplementations, unexplained anemia, peripheral neuropathy or
myleopathy, recurrent spontaneous abortions or infertility.
Testing also recommended for patients 40 years of age with coronary artery disease to exclude
homocystinuria.
Elevations in tHcy levels have also been used as an independent risk factor of coronary or cerebral
vascular disease. Treatment of moderate hyperhomocystinemia with folic acid supplementation for primary
and secondary cardiovascular protection has met with inconsistent results and at present cannot be
routinely recommended.
Limitations:
The plasma must be seprated immediately on collection to avoid continuous synthesis of Hcy  by red cells.
Samples must be immediately stored on ice and serum centrifuged immediately before a complete clot is
formed.
Certain drugs, such as anticonvulsants, methotrexate, or nitrous oxide, may interfere with the assay.
Cigarette smoking and coffee consumption increase tHcy levels.
Intraindividual variability is approximately 8%; it can be as much as 25% in patients with
hyperhomocystinemia.

Summary and Uses:
Total Hcy is a thiol-containing amino acid, produced by the intracellular demethylation of methionine to
cysteine.
Elevated levels of t Hcy may be used to exclude or confirm deficiencies of vitamin B12 or folate.
It is recommended to test in patients using medications that interfere with folate status (methotrexate,
antiepileptics), vegetarians without  B12 supplementations, unexplained anemia, peripheral neuropathy or
myleopathy, recurrent spontaneous abortions or infertility.
Testing also recommended for patients 40 years of age with coronary artery disease to exclude
homocystinuria.
Elevations in tHcy levels have also been used as an independent risk factor of coronary or cerebral
vascular disease. Treatment of moderate hyperhomocystinemia with folic acid supplementation for primary
and secondary cardiovascular protection has met with inconsistent results and at present cannot be
routinely recommended.
Limitations:
The plasma must be seprated immediately on collection to avoid continuous synthesis of Hcy  by red cells.
Samples must be immediately stored on ice and serum centrifuged immediately before a complete clot is
formed.
Certain drugs, such as anticonvulsants, methotrexate, or nitrous oxide, may interfere with the assay.
Cigarette smoking and coffee consumption increase tHcy levels.
Intraindividual variability is approximately 8%; it can be as much as 25% in patients with
hyperhomocystinemia.
Generally, a single measurement of tHcy is considered adequate.

fields.description: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy for locally advanced breast cancer
fields.recommended_treatment: Neoadjuvant Chemotherapy  Surgery  Radiation + Adjuvant Therapy
fields.rule_logic: Stage 3 BC: Neoadjuvant chemotherapy first (improves operability), then surgery, radiation, and adjuvant hormonal or targeted therapy

Stage 2 CRC: Surgery with adequate node harvest (12 nodes). Adjuvant chemotherapy considered if high-risk features (T4, poor differentiation, inadequate nodes, lymphovascular invasion). MSI/dMMR testing for immunotherapy eligibility.

fields.description: Treatment for HER2-positive early-stage breast cancer
fields.rule_logic: For stage 1 HER2+ breast cancer: surgery, radiation (if BCS), chemotherapy, HER2-targeted therapy (trastuzumab) for 1 year

fields.rule_name: Breast Cancer Stage 4 - Systemic Therapy Focus
fields.recommended_treatment: Systemic Therapy (Targeted/Immunotherapy/Chemotherapy) + Supportive Care + Palliative Radiation
fields.rule_logic: Metastatic BC: Systemic therapy based on HR/HER2 status and performance status. Endocrine therapy for HR+, HER2-targeted for HER2+, chemotherapy as backbone, consideration of immunotherapy

fields.rule_name: Colorectal Cancer Stage 4 - Palliative Systemic Therapy
fields.rule_logic: mCRC: Chemotherapy backbone (FOLFOX or FOLFIRI) + targeted agent based on RAS/BRAF/PD-L1 status. If WT RAS: EGFR inhibitor (cetuximab/panitumumab). If BRAF V600E: consider combination therapy. If MSI-H: immunotherapy consideration.

fields.recommended_treatment: Radiation Therapy + Androgen Deprivation Therapy (12-24 months)
fields.rule_logic: Intermediate-risk PCa: Radiation therapy + ADT  12-24 months preferred over surgery. Escalated dose radiation (75.6 Gy) recommended.
Stage 3 CRC: Surgery + adjuvant FOLFOX (fluorouracil, leucovorin, oxaliplatin)  6-8 months. Consider duration based on age/comorbidities. Bevacizumab may be added. Test for MMR/MSI status.

fields.description: Adjuvant chemotherapy for stage 2 breast cancer
fields.recommended_treatment: Surgery + Chemotherapy (AC or TC regimen) + Radiation + Hormonal Therapy
fields.rule_logic: Stage 2 BC: Surgery with nodal assessment, adjuvant chemotherapy (anthracycline or taxane based), radiation if needed, hormonal therapy if HR+

fields.rule_name: Lung Cancer Stage 1A NSCLC - Surgery Priority
fields.rule_logic: Stage 1A NSCLC: Lobectomy with systematic node dissection. Adjuvant chemotherapy considered in 1B-1C based on risk factors. EGFR/ALK/ROS1 testing for targeted therapy eligibility
Low-risk PCa (PSA <10, Gleason 6, T1-T2a): Excellent prognosis with AS or definitive therapy. Shared decision-making recommended. If treating: radiation or prostatectomy.

fields.rule_name: Breast Cancer Stage 1 - HR+ HER2- Standard Treatment
fields.description: Standard treatment protocol for early-stage HR+ HER2- breast cancer
fields.recommended_treatment: Surgery (Lumpectomy or Mastectomy) + Radiation + Hormonal Therapy
fields.rule_logic: For stage 1 HR+ HER2- breast cancer: surgical resection with clear margins, radiation therapy if breast-conserving surgery, tamoxifen or aromatase inhibitor for 5-10 years

fields.rule_name: Lung Cancer Stage 4 - Molecular Testing Driven
fields.description: Advanced NSCLC treatment based on molecular profile
fields.recommended_treatment: Targeted Therapy (EGFR/ALK/ROS1) or Immunotherapy or Chemotherapy
fields.rule_logic: Metastatic NSCLC: First-line treatment based on molecular profiling. EGFR mutations  TKI, ALK rearrangement  ALK inhibitor, high PD-L1  immunotherapy, No driver mutations  chemo  immunotherapy

fields.recommended_treatment: ADT (GnRH agonist/antagonist)  Docetaxel  Novel Hormonal Agents
fields.rule_logic: mHSPC: ADT is foundation. Consider docetaxel (3x weekly or weekly) with ADT based on performance status and visceral metastases. Add abiraterone or apalutamide for selected patients.
High-risk PCa: Radiation + ADT  24-36 months. Pelvic node RT if high CAPRA score. Consider prostatectomy if candidate. Consider docetaxel with ADT.

fields.rule_name: Lung Cancer Stage 3 NSCLC - Concurrent Chemorad
fields.recommended_treatment: Concurrent Chemotherapy + Radiation Therapy  Consolidation Therapy
fields.rule_logic: Stage 3 unresectable NSCLC: Concurrent cisplatin-based chemotherapy and radiation therapy. Consolidation with durvalumab (PACIFIC trial). Check PD-L1 status for immunotherapy timing.

common_side_effects.name: Fatigue
common_side_effects.management: Get plenty of rest, prioritize tasks, and take breaks when needed. Engage in gentle exercises like yoga or short walks to help boost energy
common_side_effects.description: Feeling extremely tired or weak, making everyday activities more challenging
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If fatigue is severe, interferes with daily activities, or is accompanied by other concerning symptoms like shortness of breath or chest pain

common_side_effects.name: Nausea and Vomiting
common_side_effects.management: Eat small, frequent meals, avoid strong smells, and stay hydrated by drinking plenty of fluids. Consider using anti-nausea medication as prescribed by your doctor
common_side_effects.description: Feeling queasy or experiencing vomiting, which can lead to dehydration and discomfort
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If nausea and vomiting are severe, persistent, or accompanied by signs of dehydration like excessive thirst or dark urine

common_side_effects.name: Hair Loss
common_side_effects.management: Use gentle hair care products, consider wearing a wig or hat, and protect your scalp from the sun. Be patient, as hair often grows back after treatment ends
common_side_effects.description: Losing hair on the scalp, eyebrows, or other parts of the body due to treatment
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If hair loss is accompanied by other concerning symptoms like itching, redness, or skin irritation

common_side_effects.name: Mouth Sores
common_side_effects.management: Use a soft-bristled toothbrush, avoid spicy or acidic foods, and rinse with saltwater or a prescribed mouthwash. Apply topical pain relievers as directed by your doctor
common_side_effects.description: Experiencing painful sores or ulcers in the mouth, making eating and drinking uncomfortable
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If mouth sores are severe, bleeding, or accompanied by fever or difficulty swallowing

common_side_effects.name: Diarrhea
common_side_effects.management: Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of fluids, avoid spicy or fatty foods, and consider taking anti-diarrheal medication as prescribed by your doctor
common_side_effects.description: Experiencing loose, watery stools, which can lead to dehydration and discomfort
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If diarrhea is severe, bloody, or accompanied by signs of dehydration like excessive thirst or dark urine

common_side_effects.name: Constipation
common_side_effects.management: Increase fiber intake, stay hydrated, and engage in regular physical activity. Consider using stool softeners or laxatives as directed by your doctor
common_side_effects.description: Experiencing infrequent or difficult bowel movements, which can cause discomfort and bloating
common_side_effects.when_to_call: If constipation is severe, accompanied by abdominal pain, or persists for an extended period
